page.title: 01LANDSCAPE.
page.content: Landscape: The major feature of the block is undulating farmland coupled with areas of mixed woodland. the area generally comprises the foothills of the Pennines. The River Etherow crosses the area diagonally from Northeast to Southwest, effectively separating the block into two halves.The valley of the Etherow has been developed into a popular Country Park with one of its main entry points in the village of Compstall. The block is partly in Stockport, Greater Manchester and partly in the High Peak of Derbyshire. It is an area of great natural beauty.
